| SubAssembly | Concrete | – | POCO derived from Product. |
| FinishedProduct | Concrete | – | POCO derived from Product. |
| ManufacturingProcess | Concrete | – | Data holder for process with Operations collection. |
| WorkCenter | Concrete | – | Holds Machines; no behavior. |
| Machine | Concrete | – | Linked to WorkCenter. |
| Operator | Concrete | – | Linked via OperationOperator join. |
| WorkOrder | Concrete | – | Aggregate-like root for Operations/Traceability; no domain services. |
| Operation | Concrete | – | Step with refs to process/work center/work order. |
| OperationOperator | Concrete | – | Join entity (many-to-many). |
| ShopFloorExecution | Concrete | – | Container for WorkOrders. |
| ComplianceCert | Concrete | – | Uses rowversion for concurrency. |
| InventoryLot | Concrete | – | Traceability relationships. |
| Warehouse | Concrete | – | Collection of InventoryLots. |
| CustomerOrder | Concrete | – | Links to FinishedProduct and Shipments. |
| Shipment | Concrete | – | Links to CustomerOrder; traceability records. |
| TraceabilityRecord | Concrete | – | Event record linked to multiple entities. |
| SupplierContract | Concrete | – | Rowversion concurrency, ties to RawMaterial. |
| BillOfMaterials | Concrete | – | Aggregate root with Items; uses TPT inheritance via Product. |
| BillOfMaterialsItem | Concrete | – | Join entity to Product. |
| EngineeringDesign | Concrete | – | Root with CADModel/Drawing/Revision collections. |
| CADModel | Concrete | – | Linked to EngineeringDesign. |
| Drawing | Concrete | – | Linked to EngineeringDesign. |
| Revision | Concrete | – | Linked to EngineeringDesign. |
| Engineer | Concrete | – | Many-to-many with EngineeringDesign. |
| LcpUml8Context | Concrete | Unit of Work (EF DbContext) | Coordinates EF change tracking and SaveChanges/transactions. |
| QualityAssurance | Concrete | – | Root for InspectionPlans; product associations. |
| InspectionPlan | Concrete | – | Child of QualityAssurance; change orders collection. |
| InspectionResult | Concrete | – | Child of InspectionPlan; traceability records. |
| NonConformance | Concrete | – | Child of InspectionResult. |
| CorrectiveAction | Concrete | – | Child of NonConformance. |
| WorkOrdersController | Concrete | – | Transaction script over DbContext; no abstraction. |
| ProductsController | Concrete | Simple Factory | Switch on "'`Type` to instantiate correct Product subtype; also uses optimistic concurrency token. |
| ChangeOrder | Concrete | – | Links to Product, EngineeringDesign, WorkOrder, InspectionPlan. |
| QualityAssuranceController | Concrete | – | Transaction script with explicit DB transactions. |
| ShopFloorExecutionsController | Concrete | – | Transaction script managing WorkOrder links. |
| EngineeringDesignsController | Concrete | – | Transaction script with lifecycle state changes. |

Total classes counted: 38
Patterns found: 2 (Unit of Work via DbContext; Simple Factory in ProductsController)
Pattern density: 2 / 38 = 0.053 (5.3%)

SOLID/Decoupling grade: C-
- Controllers depend directly on EF DbContext and entities (no Repository/Service abstractions), reducing dependency inversion.
- Business rules live in controllers (transaction scripts), so SRP and Open/Closed are weak; changes to workflows require controller edits.
- Entities are anemic data carriers; behavior is not co-located with data, risking violations of encapsulation.
- Some positives: DbContext scopes transactions/unit-of-work; optimistic concurrency token on products; clear aggregate boundaries in entities.
